Today I really didn't want to show up on the mat. But I did not want to ruin my 14 day streak, so here I am, in the middle of the night, doing day 15 and hating it. And then when I am in shavasana, I feel grateful for showing up. I feel great, and my hips feel really good. For fun, I decide to carefully try full lotus (have never been able to do it). First side, notice I am very close actually, am slightly amazed. Second side, still feeling great, and carefully, I slide into full lotus. I only stayed there for 2 seconds since I don't want to overdo it, but thank you. This journey is very transforming, and I feel more in touch with yoga than I have done since the beginning of the pandemic. I know this is an old video series, but it is still amazing. Day 15: Yoga with Adriene - Half Hour Half Moon Practice. Phew. That was an intense session. We're reminded that even without weight equipment we can still get a good workout in. This was a demanding session today. There was a lot of lunges, and quite a few warrior two poses. These awaken a good burn in the thighs and get the blood pumping. Then we come to the end and the half moon poses.  This poses are rather difficult, at least for me, being new to my yoga practice. It was a struggle maintaining my balance, and keeping 80% of myself suspended in the air while trying to open my chest and breathing. My legs wound up shaking like a magnitude 6 earthquake was happening beneath my feet. I fought through the poses and cajoled myself to follow along and keep up, in my under-dogged need for a good challenge. Being done now, with a little bit of soreness throughout my body, I'm once more happy with myself, and a bit proud for keeping up with this so far and rising to the challenge. Thank you for a wonderful session Adriene! Namaste.

This morning, I felt like I NEEDED to yoga, but I didn't really WANT to. I'm visiting my parents, and I hadn't made it to the mat in a couple of days, so I was out of the routine, but also kinda wanted to get back into it. I woke up tired and already late for the day. I was moving slow, and I have lots of homework and housework and such. Yoga felt like the first of several responsibilities I wanted to avoid. But at the beginning, Adriene reminded me to put off anything on my to do list that might get in the way (how does she always know???) and so I did. IT WAS SO WORTH IT!!!! I was just reminded today why I love yoga and why I always come back to the mat!! I had never done half-moon pose in all of my years of yoga, but Adriene made it look easy (shocker, it wasn't!) but it felt amazing to work on it, and pay attention to my body and just FIND WHAT FEELS GOOD! Thank you, Adrien, for doing what you do!!!

Also I thought the block was mandatory, but when I typed half moon on Google no one uses a block...

This was tough. I found myself becoming frustrated during half-moon because I wasn't able to balance at all, not even for a second. Yet, each time Adriene reminded me that this was a playtime, a time to explore your body and stretch it out, and I found myself slowly relaxing and pushing back that frustration. I may not be able to do half-moon right now but maybe one day I can with enough practice. The rest of the practice was enough to make me sweat haha but it was a good sweat. I feel accomplished and proud of myself for sticking through with the poses even as my thighs started shaking. I just want to say to anyone who may be doubting their strength that is ok to not be perfect. Every time you come back and do your best, whatever that may be, is a time you can grow. It is important to believe in yourself and know your worth no matter where you are in your journey.
